results.name: Highest minimal Hamming distance of any Type 4^H+ Hermitian additive self-dual code over GF(4) of length n.
comment: The sequence continues: a(23) = 8 or 9, a(24) = 8, 9 or 10, a(25) = 8 or 9, ...
reference: P. Gaborit and A. Otmani, Experimental construction of self-dual codes, Preprint.
link: G. Nebe, E. M. Rains and N. J. A. Sloane, Self-Dual Codes and Invariant Theory, Springer, Berlin, 2006.
A. R. Calderbank, E. M. Rains, P. W. Shor and N. J. A. Sloane, Quantum error correction via codes over GF(4), IEEE Trans. Inform. Theory, 44 (1998), 1369-1387.
E. M. Rains and N. J. A. Sloane, Self-dual codes, pp. 177-294 of Handbook of Coding Theory, Elsevier, 1998; (Abstract, pdf, ps).
xref: A105687 gives the number of codes with this minimal distance.
